- Create new virtual machine for Domain Controller (Windows server 2016) and click next
- Browse to the iso image of windows server 2016
- Name the Virtual Machine.
- Select BIOS, number of Processors , allocate 4gb RAM
- Use Network adapter Translation.
- Select LSI logic.
- Select NVme for disk type.
- Select create a new virtual disk. 
- Set Disk space of 60 GB and click Next and Finish
- Windows server 2016 -> Under hardware -> floppy -> uncheck connect at power on and use floppy image file. 
- In processors -> check virtualize intel and virtualize IOMU
- power on virtual machine of Windows server 2016 
- Select English US -> Next -> Install
- Select Windows server 2016 Datacenter Evaluation -> Next 
- Type username and password and Finish
- Once windows starts type the password
- Open server manager Click on add roles and feature and click Next
- Select role based or feature based installation.
- Select server from server pool. 
- Select active directory domain service and click Next then Install
- Click on the yellow flag in server manager and promote to domain controller 
- Select add a new forest and give your domain name
- Give a password for for your domain controller click next and install
- In vmware workstation go to esxi and set static ip addreses to connect the domain (Windows server 2016) 
- Go to dns configuration and write the domain
-  the active directory is activated. with domain name
